episodes.title: Gyojintou no Ou: Kaishin Neptune!
episodes.plot: Straw Hat Pirates are in a town on Fishman Island and King Neptune and Megalo appear to invite the Straw Hats to Ryugu Palace.

episodes.title: Ryuuguujou! Tasuketa Same ni Tsurerarete
episodes.plot: Luffy, Nami, Usopp, Brook, Camie, and Pappag travel with King Neptune to Ryugu Palace.

episodes.title: Yowamushi de Nakimushi! Koukakutou no Ningyo Hime
episodes.plot: Vander Decken IX reveals that he plans to marry the princess, using his Mark-Mark Fruit curse to throw a giant axe at her.

episodes.title: Kinkyuu Jitai Hassei: Senkyo Sareta Ryuuguujou
episodes.plot: The guards around Zoro and the others are preparing to pop their air bubble, however, Nami found some bubbly coral and made the whole room fill with air and Zoro prepares to fight Neptune.

episodes.title: Ryuuguujou Gekishin! Shirahoshi Yuukai Jiken
episodes.plot: Luffy leads Shirahoshi out of her tower inside Megalo while Brook and the Minister of the Right tells them to stop.

episodes.title: Hody Shuurai: Fukushuu Keikaku no Hajimari
episodes.plot: Luffy is still on his way to the Sea Forest with Shirahoshi, when he notices something going to the Ryugu Palace, which is revealed to be Hody and Vander Decken IX.

episodes.title: Ryuuguujou no Kessen! Zoro Tai Hody
episodes.plot: Neptune begs someone to protect her daughter. Hody just comments on how weak he is and states he only joined his army for military strength and knowledge. He states he will revive the dream and ambition of Arlong.

episodes.title: Shirahoshi o Mamore: Decken no Tsuigeki
episodes.plot: Chopper tries to persuade Sanji to not turn around, or else he will see Shirahoshi and die. But Sanji turns around and after seeing the princess, turns into stone.

episodes.title: Ichimi Haiboku!? Hody Ryuuguujou Seiatsu
episodes.plot: Zoro cuts Hody and asks for Neptune's help to escape from Ryugu Palace. Unfortunately, Hody who was unconscious comes to his senses after taking an Energy Steroid and successfully stops Neptune and the Straw Hats from escaping.

episodes.title: Yomigaeru Innen! Nami to Gyojin Kaizokudan!
episodes.plot: Robin continues her search while the New Fishman Pirates begin to take over. People are also seen being forced to step on a photo, and if they do not, they are considered as enemies.

episodes.title: Dorei Kaihou no Eiyuu: Boukenka Tiger
episodes.plot: Otohime confronts a robber who was stealing money so he could buy food for his ten children. Otohime and Jinbe try to change Fishman island, and Jinbe leaves the Army to join the Sun Pirates.

episodes.title: Kizaru Toujou! Tiger o Nerau Wana!
episodes.plot: Entering a flashback, Neptune holds a baby Shirahoshi commenting on Tiger's attack on Mary Geoise, stating he would not be able to attend a summit for a long time because of it.

episodes.title: Team Kessei! Chopper o Sukue
episodes.plot: Toriko and Komatsu are seen fishing when Komatsu catches a Harusame. After defeating it, Luffy suddenly comes out of the Harusame's mouth and surprises Toriko and Komatsu.

episodes.title: Eiyuu no Saigo: Tiger Shougeki no Shinjitsu
episodes.plot: The Sun Pirates start making their way to Koala's hometown, while giving her a slight makeover, new clothes and cutting her hair. on their ship, Koala still acts like a slave would, doing chores without being asked and asking for orders.

episodes.title: Kaizokudan Bunretsu: Jinbe Tai Arlong
episodes.plot: After Fisher Tiger's death, Arlong, enraged, betrays his last wishes and decides to attack and kill villagers of Koala's village for selling him out, upon trying he is easily beaten by Vice-Admiral Borsalino and taken into Marine custody.

episodes.title: Yureru Gyojintou! Hyouchaku Shita Tenryuubito
episodes.plot: With Jinbe having been accepted as a Shichibukai, the Sun Pirates return to Fishman Island.

episodes.title: Totsuzen no Higeki! Mirai o Tozasu Kyoudan
episodes.plot: Vander Decken IX discovers about the Tamatebako and wishes to use it to age Shirahoshi after she grows up a little.

episodes.title: Futatabi Genzai e! Ugokidasu Hody
episodes.plot: After Otohime passed away, Hody Jones had found and killed the suspected human assassin and showed him to the people.

episodes.title: Oukoku Gekishin: Neptune Shokei Shirei
episodes.plot: Hody makes his announcement to take over the Ryugu Kingdom with the execution of King Neptune as the start of his new rule. Hody also announces that he will kill Straw Hats so that they will serve as example to all humans in the surface.

episodes.title: Shoujita Kiretsu! Luffy Tai Jinbe
episodes.plot: Luffy and Jinbe start their duel to see who gets to fight Hody, but their fight was cut short by Sanji's and Robin's interference.

episodes.title: Hody no Ihen: Kyouyaku no Shin no Chikara!
episodes.plot: The New Fishman Pirates head to the Gyoncorde Plaza to execute King Neptune but before getting at the plaza, they demonstrate a little taste of their power by terrorizing and destroying everything in their path.

episodes.title: Kessen Hajimaru: Gyoncorde Hiroba!
episodes.plot: Neptune's army put up an attempt to stop Hody Jones and his pirates from reaching Gyoncorde Plaza but seeing the king held hostage prevents them from attacking.

episodes.title: Shougeki no Kokuhaku: Otohime Ansatsu no Shinjitsu
episodes.plot: Jinbe and Shirahoshi are captured by the New Fishman Pirates when they fall into a trap due to a balloon version of King Neptune which easily tricks Shirahoshi and Megalo.

episodes.title: Shirahoshi no Namida! Luffy Tsui ni Toujou
episodes.plot: Shirahoshi reveals that Megalo witnessed Hody shooting Queen Otohime and told her in secret.

episodes.title: Dai Gekitotsu! Mugiwara Ichimi VS 10 Man no Teki
episodes.plot: The citizens celebrate at the arrival of Luffy and his crew. Jinbe comments on how his plan with the Straw Hat Pirates crew worked. Luffy takes down half of Hody's forces with Haki.

episodes.title: Oowaza Sakuretsu! Zoro Sanji Shutsugeki!
episodes.plot: The Straw Hat Pirates begin their attack with Luffy, Zoro and Sanji taking the lead in the fight but mostly it is the latter two of the three who begin showing their new powers and abilities from their two year separation and training.

episodes.title: Hatsu Hirou! Sunny Gou no Himitsu Heiki!
episodes.plot: The battle rages on between the Straw Hats and the New Fishman Pirates. Sanji and Zoro are competing over who can take down the most fishmen.

episodes.title: Iron Pirate! Franky Shougun Toujou
episodes.plot: The battle between the New Fishman Pirates and the Straw Hats continues, with the Straw Hats gaining the upper hand. Seeing this, Daruma decides to join the fight, targeting the Brachio Tank V and collapsing the ground underneath it.

episodes.title: Noah Sekkin! Gyojintou Kaimetsu no Kiki!
episodes.plot: Luffy and Hody continue their fight with Luffy getting the upper hand with Haki and Hody's attacks being ineffective against Luffy.

episodes.title: Isoge Luffy! Shirahoshi Zettaizetsumei
episodes.plot: Shirahoshi begins swimming out to sea in an attempt to lure the ark Noah away and save Fishman Island, while Luffy gets Sanji's help to allow him to reach the ship's chains and stop Hody.

episodes.title: Gekitou Kaishi! Luffy Tai Hody!
episodes.plot: Hody takes his trident out of Vander Decken's body and, after a short fight, Decken is defeated. Then Hody goes after Shirahoshi, slicing through Ryuboshi and Manboshi, reaches her with his incomparable underwater speed, and grabs her hair.

episodes.title: Dairansen! Ichimi Tai Shin Gyojin Kaizokudan!
episodes.plot: Luffy along with the three princes try to protect Shirahoshi against Hody Jones.

episodes.title: Luffy Haiboku!? Hody Fukushuu no Toki
episodes.plot: As the Noah falls onto the Fishman Island, Shirahoshi desperately tries to tell Decken to wake up only for Hody to attack her but Manboshi takes the blunt of the attack.

episodes.title: Shougeki no Jijitsu! Hody no Shoutai!
episodes.plot: The story goes back before the Noah started falling back to the island. Jinbe and Sanji continue to fight Wadatsumi and Wadatsumi becomes angry and inflates himself, crushing some of his allies unknowingly.

episodes.title: Zero ni! Luffy e no Atsuki Negai!
episodes.plot: Hody's past is revealed and Luffy continues his fight with him.

episodes.title: Luffy Konshin no Ichigeki! Red Hawk Sakuretsu
episodes.plot: Brook continues to fight Zeo and reveals his new control over his Yomi Yomi no Mi abilities. Usopp continues to fight Daruma and has set traps for him.

episodes.title: Tsui ni Kecchaku! Hody Saishuu Kessen
episodes.plot: Hody recovers thanks to the Energy Steroids and manages to overwhelm Luffy and bite him again in the same spot.

episodes.title: Tomare Noah! Kesshi no Elephant Gatling!
episodes.plot: All of the New Fishman Pirates lie down defeated while the Straw Hat Pirates are relaxing and waiting for Luffy.

episodes.title: Mirai e! Taiyou e to Tsuzuku Michi!
episodes.plot: With the Sea Kings having stopped and saved the great ship Noah, Shirahoshi learns a startling secret from the Sea Kings.

episodes.title: Akasareta Himitsu: Kodai Heiki no Shinjitsu
episodes.plot: As the whole Fishman Island celebrates the capture and defeat of Hody and the New Fishman Pirates by the Straw Hats, who make their own plans to leave Fishman Island soon.

episodes.title: Ichimi Kyougaku! Aratanaru Kaigun Gensui!
episodes.plot: King Neptune talks about the Ancient Weapons with Shirahoshi and Nico Robin while Caribou listens and makes his way to Shirahoshi's room.

episodes.title: Okashizuki! Yonkou Big Mom
episodes.plot: The rest of the Straw Hats are waiting for Luffy, Zoro, and Sanji to return the treasure from Caribou. They find Caribou easily with all the treasure.

episodes.title: Zento Tanan: Shin Sekai ni Machiukeru Wana
episodes.plot: The Minister of the Right was thanking the Straw Hats for saving Fishman Island, when suddenly he got a report that the Tamate Box is gone and is in the hands of Baron Tamago and Pekoms.

episodes.title: Tsui ni Shukkou! Sayonara Gyojin-tou
episodes.plot: The mermaids and Keimi from the Mermaid Cafe ask Madam Shyarly if they can say good bye to the Straw Hats. Madam Shyarly says that her prediction that Luffy will destroy Fishman Island was wrong since they defeated Hody and his Pirates.

episodes.title: Shin Sekai e! Saikyou no Umi o Mezashite
episodes.plot: The Straw Hats are Heading into the New World.

episodes.title: Z no Yabou Hen: Chiisana Kyojin Lily!
episodes.plot: The Straw Hats find themselves in a middle of an infamous sea in the New World known for its mirages and outrageous weather patterns.

episodes.title: Z no Yabou Hen: Nazo no Saikyou Gundan Toujou!
episodes.plot: Nami creates a plan for the Straw Hats to rescue Lily's father, Panz Fry. Chopper, Robin, Brook, and Luffy are the diversion group while Usopp, Sanji, Zoro, and Lily are in the submarine.

episodes.title: Z no Yabou Hen: Kesshi no Dai Dasshutsu Sakusen!
episodes.plot: Luffy and Zoro face off against Shuzo and Momonga. The Straw Hats, Lily, and her father manage to escape with a Coup de Burst and the anchor connected to the Thousand Sunny.

episodes.title: Z no Yabou Hen: Luffy VS Shuzo!
episodes.plot: Shuzo orders his men to be launched at the island like torpedoes and sacrifice themselves for him.
